programme.desc: Beppe Faresin is an extreme kayaker with a dream: venturing into the Gulf of Mexico on a kayak. In this adventure, he will kayak his way through the Mexican lagoons and swamps to discover the wild nature of this unique country. Faresin is already famous for raising funds for UNICEF while paddling in rivers and oceans all over the world. Now, he faces a new challenge: crossing the Gulf of Mexico by himself. For almost 1500 km, this apparently fearless athlete will discover corners of Mexico otherwise unreachable by land. Follow his challenge navigating through the Gulf and find out what happens along the way.

programme.title: Ride To the Roots
programme.desc: RIDE TO THE ROOTS is a simple format for a documentary series on athletes and artists. Perfect to profile characters with a unique upbringing, personal background, origin or past. Each episode focuses on an athlete, artist or person of interest as they return to their hometown. In an exciting and emotional trip down memory lane, our protagonist encounters the important people in their life (family, friends, coaches, lovers), revisits the key locations (schools, training centers, homes, fields) and reveals exclusive personal stills, footage and recordings. We will discover the moments that shaped their career, taking them on a rollercoaster ride from childhood passion to professional success.
